glosses: To become unable to move due to sinking into mud, sand, snow etc.

etymology: From Ottoman Turkish صاپلانمق (ṣaplanmaḳ, “to become possessed of a handle, to stick in or into, to sink and stick into mud”), derived from Proto-Turkic *sapla- (“to attach a handle”), from Proto-Turkic *sap (“hilt of a knife or sword”), morphologically sap + -la + -n + -mak.
